{"article_id":"dvgtI6ESy2tf2Smb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Puerto Rico has now endured the longest power failure in U.S. history ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"after Category 4 Hurricane Maria tore a path of destruction across the island on Sept. 20 .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"One of the contracts","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"the island 's beleaguered government signed","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"in order to get the lights turned back on","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"is with a tiny Montana-based company","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"named Whitefish Energy .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"The contract , worth $ 300 million , calls for Whitefish","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"- which employed just 2 employees as of late last month -","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"to repair power lines","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to connect critical infrastructure .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"The no-bid contract with a tiny , inexperienced company","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"that happens to be based in the hometown of Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"has raised eyebrows in Congress and Puerto Rico ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"where multiple investigations are now underway","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to determine","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"how the contract was awarded .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"A company with just 2 employees is now in charge of restoring electricity in Puerto Rico","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"Late Thursday , the signed contract was leaked","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and posted online .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"It shows","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that what at first appeared to be a shady deal is actually an unbelievably shady deal .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"The signed contract ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"which has not yet been independently authenticated by ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"was uploaded to Document Cloud","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"and shared ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"but removed for unknown reasons around 11 a.m . ET on Friday .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"We reported this story","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"using the contract","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"as uploaded ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"prior to it being taken down .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"We need answers on the Whitefish Energy contract and any others like it .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"I 'm grateful @ kenklippenstein has brought the story to light .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Journalism matters .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Journalism makes a difference .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"And public officials must act on what they uncover","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"or we are failing our responsibility .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"https : //t.co/XXztUFyXJc","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"- Raja Krishnamoorthi","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"( @ CongressmanRaja )","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"October 27 , 2017","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"The contract itself matched details","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"reported in other news accounts ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"and Congress is already taking action","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"based on these provisions ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"which are unusual .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"First , there is language","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"that prohibits the Puerto Rican Electric Power Authority ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"known as PREPA ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"as well as the Puerto Rican government , the head of FEMA , and even the Comptroller General of the U.S. to audit or review the prices","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"that Whitefish is charging under the contract ,","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"or the profits","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"it is earning .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"In no event shall PREPA , the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico , the FEMA Administrator , the Comptroller General of the United States , or any of their authorized representatives have the right","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"to audit or review the cost and profit elements of the labor rates","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"specified herein .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Boom .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Leaked copy of the Puerto Rico / Whitefish contract :","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"https : //t.co/XR1wTcD5hJ","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"- Ken Klippenstein","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"( @ kenklippenstein )","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"October 27 , 2017","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"This is especially noteworthy","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"considering the prices","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"the company is charging Puerto Rico ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"which is a U.S. territory","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"that was forced to declare a form of bankruptcy in May ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"and whose economy was further decimated by the storm .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"The wages and equipment charges in this contract are extremely high .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"According to the contract ,","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"site supervisors are earning $ 330 an hour for their work ,","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"while project accountants are earning $ 440 per hour .","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"The lowest-paid workers ,","depth":15},{"id":74,"text":"according to the contract ,","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"are making $ 140.26 an hour .","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"By comparison , minimum wage in Puerto Rico is $ 7.25 an hour .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"According to Indeed.com ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"the average salary for a journeyman electrical lineman is $ 39.03 per hour in the continental U.S .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"However , a journeyman lineman on Whitefish Energy 's Puerto Rico project will earn $ 277.88 per hour .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Because some of the power lines are only accessible via helicopter","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"or require equipment to be airlifted by such aircraft ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"the bid schedule also includes information on those costs .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"While there is less","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"to compare it to ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"these prices also seem quite steep .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"For example , Whitefish Energy is charging Puerto Rico nearly $ 4,000 per hour for a small helicopter","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"known as the MD-500 .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"A heavy lift Chinook helicopter will cost PREPA far more , on the order of $ 20,000 per hour of flight time .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"The contract requires","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"that PREPA pay Whitefish Energy within 10 days","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"of receiving an invoice ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"which may be a tall order ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"considering the state of infrastructure on the island and the power authority 's dwindling financial reserves .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Such payments have to be made","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"even if Whitefish is late","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"in completing its work .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Contractor will use commercially reasonable efforts","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"to perform the work in such a manner","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to meet scheduling expectations ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"but PREPA waives any claim against Contractor","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"related to delayed completion of the work .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"While at least two congressional committees are already moving forward with investigations","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"of how this contract was awarded ,","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"it 's unclear what Congress can do","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"to change it .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"As the contract states ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"this is a deal between PREPA and Whitefish Energy ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"with the federal government playing no role .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"The Federal Government is not a party to this Contract","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"and is not subject to any obligations or liabilities to PREPA , Contractor , or any other party","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"pertaining to any matter","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"resulting from the Contract .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"FEMA , for its part , says","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"even though it had nothing to do with the contract in the first place ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"it is examining it","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"since payments would likely come out of disaster relief payments to PREPA .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"FEMA statement on Whitefish Energy :","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"`` FEMA has significant concerns with how PREPA procured this contract ''","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"pic.twitter.com/rMHkzDxqKS","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"- NBC News","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"( @ NBCNews )","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"October 27 , 2017","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"`` Based on initial review and information from PREPA ,","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"FEMA has significant concerns with how PREPA procured this contract","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"and has not confirmed","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"whether the contract prices are reasonable , ''","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"the agency said in a statement .","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"According to FEMA ,","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"no public assistance reimbursements have yet been made to PREPA","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"that would then go to Whitefish Energy .","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"As of Oct. 27 , more than five weeks after Hurricane Maria struck Puerto Rico ,","depth":2},{"id":133,"text":"72 percent of the island still lacks electricity .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":267,"left":265,"right":266,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":265,"left":251,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":1